commit.message:
Add meta for options

This allows options to have additional data when declared. This allows
you to tag or markup options with things like "this one is a secret,
so when logging configuration, don't print it".

Fixes #88

commit.message:
Fix nested BoundConfig case

In a situation where there are nested BoundConfigs in the config chain, then
parents configs will raise a KeyError because that key isn't in *their*
options.

This fixes that by removing BoundConfigs from the chain.

This also adds __repr__ which will make things easier to debug in complex
config scenarios.
